Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! Catastrophic for Sri Lanka and Dimuth Karunaratne will be livid while walking off the field. Mitchell Santner tosses the ball up on middle, Karunaratne comes forward and flicks it wide of Glenn Phillips at mid-wicket and starts to run. Dinesh Chandimal is caught ball-watching and Karunaratne has to scurry back while almost being at the bowler's end. Phillips makes a fine stop but his throw at the keeper's end is a weak one. Thankfully for New Zealand, Tom Latham is at short leg and he picks up the ball before flicking it back onto the stumps. The stand of 122 runs is broken as Karunaratne departs for 46.
Default_Commentary: 39.1: Mitchell Santner to Dimuth Karunaratne, OUT! run out (Glenn Phillips / Tom Latham).
Howout: run out (Glenn Phillips / Tom Latham)
